Title: Shetland Wool Jacket - Clay Check

Title: Patchwork Wool Jacket
Body (HTML): <sections><section id="1"><sectionTitle>Details</sectionTitle><sectionBody>Do you need a Patchwork Wool Jacket for your fall and wintering needs I mean no one needs this jacket in the literal sense just like you didn t need to see the last 30 movies that you saw but they gave your life a sense of color and fun and jubilation and that s why life is worth living not to just eat off brand cereal and move through life like a cow chewing cud Vibrancy joy these are things worth living for and if you re considering this jacket then you probably already know this and then maybe you do need this jacket This is all a bit overwrought and arm chair philosophizing but that s what makes clothes so much fun and this is a fun jacket Regardless this is a custom milled 100 wool made in Portugal and then tailored in India 100 Wool Shetland Tailored in India Responsibility What does responsibility mean People talk a lot about transparency and sustainability I think the sum is responsibility For Corridor this means that we actually work in the factory with the tailors every season to create the garments and ensure the workshops are environmentally certified ISO 9001 and socially accountable SA 8000 You can feel good knowing where and how the garment was made This item is final sale and is non returnable</sectionBody></section><section id="2"><sectionTitle>Size & Fit</sectionTitle><sectionBody>Click buy for more sizing information.</sectionBody></section><section id="3"><sectionTitle>Shipping & Returns</sectionTitle><sectionBody></sectionBody></section></sections>

Title: Organic Highland Wool Crewneck - Harbor Grey
Body (HTML): <sections><section id="1"><sectionTitle>Details</sectionTitle><sectionBody>The Organic Highland Crewneck is made from organic un dyed wool from Highland Wool Sheep in Peru This is the natural color of the sheep s wool and is not processed or dyed before it s spun and knit into sweaters in our partner workshop in Peru Highland wool is extremely warm because it s cold in the Peruvian Highland so if it s warm enough for these sheep it should work well for you on the coldest days Our shoulder shape is specific and utilizes a vintage hammer shoulder rather than a traditional raglan for a stronger more flattering shape Manufacturing Knitting Partner made responsibly in partnership with Eunice Moran s workshop in Lima Peru Yarn 100 organic un dyed wool This item is final sale and is non returnable</sectionBody></section><section id="2"><sectionTitle>Size & Fit</sectionTitle><sectionBody>Click buy for more sizing information.</sectionBody></section><section id="3"><sectionTitle>Shipping & Returns</sectionTitle><sectionBody></sectionBody></section></sections>
